paragraph.def:
“consular
                        post” means any consulate-general, consulate, vice-consulate or
                    consular agency;

“member of the administrative and technical staff of the
                        consular post” means any person who performs administrative or
                    technical services at the consular post;

“family
                        members” means the spouse, minor children and parents who live in the
                    same household with and are dependent on a member of the consular post;

“national of the sending State” means any natural person having the
                    nationality of the sending State, and, when applicable, also means any juridical
                    person of the sending State;

paragraph.content:
concerning private immovable property situated in the territory of the
                    receiving State, unless the consular officer holds it on behalf of the sending
                    State and for the purposes of the consular post;

consular premises and residences of the members of the consular post
                    acquired in the name of the sending State or its representative and transactions
                    or instruments related thereto;
